					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In Contra, just to have an example, the game slows down when there's a lot of action happening.  What if invisible sprites (or whatever) were added in whenever a lot of action <em>isn't</em> happening in order to keep the game constantly running at &quot;slowdown&quot; speed, and then the overall speed of the game was just &quot;turned up&quot;?  By that, I mean like each moving object in the game is modified to move faster.  As in, every single velocity (or is it just speed?) setting is recalculated.  Also, the music would be resequenced to play at a faster tempo.  Okay, this may not be <em>feasible</em>, but is this at least possible?  Or am I missing something?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

