				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">lda #$ff<br />waste_time:<br />dec<br />bne waste_time</div><br />Just like I said in <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=107830#p107830" class="postlink">another thread</a> earlier today: why guess arbitrary delays when the system gives you all the information you need? Think about it: you have a dummy loop that wastes 10,000 cycles hoping that this will make frames with few enemies take longer, but what happens on busy frames? You'll most likely get 3 repeated frames, instead of 2. Not so &quot;always in 30fps slowdown mode&quot; now is it?<br /><br />The PPU tells you when each frame is rendered, so just count the freaking VBlanks. Every other VBlank you update the PPU so it can draw a new frame, otherwise just return from the interrupt and let the game logic continue. This will get you a steady 30fps (unless things get insanely busy to the point where 2 frames aren't enough to process a single game frame).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

